article.headline: UTEP 79, Houston 71
article.story: EL PASO, Texas (AP) -- Stefon Jackson scored 21 points and grabbed 17 rebounds as Texas-El Paso snapped a three-game losing streak by beating Houston 79-71 Saturday night. UTEP (13-10, 5-4 Conference USA) held Houston (11-10, 5-3) to 31 percent shooting from the floor. The Cougars saw their five-game winning streak come to an end. Dion Dowell scored 21 points for Houston and Oliver Lafayette had 12 points and nine rebounds. UTEP's Darren Clarke hit 5-of-7 shots and scored 13 points off the bench. UTEP outscored Houston 25-7 in bench points. Houston's Robert McIver had 10 points, and UTEP's Marvin Kilgore had 10 points and six assists.
